on Brooklyn and immerse us in a community defined by work, family, and ethnic ties.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aStreet photography. 4aNew York History. 4aPhotography. 4aUrban Studies.  aBrooklyn, Change, Neighborhood, Family, Religion, Working Class, Blue Collar.1 aRacioppo, Larry, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRobbins, Tom, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aVan Haaften, Julia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2018z978311060655340uhttps://doi.org/10.7591/978150172677440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501726774423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501726774/original  a978-3-11-060655-3  Cornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_PPALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles